snippet.textDisplay:
Dear Sam Smith

When I heard ‘To Die For’ I related at first. I related because I thought I too needed somebody to die for. I might have someone like that in my life at the moment and I wish everyone has. But even so we all  think at some point that we are alone.

To quote you, looking at those couples sipping Pink Lemonade on Sundays, holding hands and having picture frames to flaunt, it hurts if you don’t have someone to do all those with. But why need someone to die for; Just for them to have to move on and do better when you do really give your life?

I’d beg to differ. i think if you really need someone then why can’t it be somebody to live for ? Somebody to actually think about holding on for even  though it feels like it’s not worth to anymore? Does one’s love is only proven when you can give your life for them? I like to think differently and I too really wish  I had someone to die for, and so I said I might even have someone like that.

But won’t we rather find somebody to count the days with, to take this rollercoaster of a ride called with, to take all those chances that we wouldn’t if we were to take them all alone. Maybe to live for them  first and then for ourselves.

Because life is a journey where we learn something different everyday, but with someone to spend it with learning new things feels like it has a purpose. As if our own lives itself has a purpose.

Much love 

Ditsa//

snippet.textDisplay: This song just popped up as an ad while I was listening to some music on youtubemusic. 2 days ago was my 20th bday, not a single person remembered it, I was all alone in my room. Additionally last year me and my girl broke up, we had been together for almost three years and she was like a sister to me. When I heard that song I instantly started to cry because the song made me realise what my biggest fear is: to be alone and forgotten. Thank you Sam it is a wonderful song.
